DebugRequest
prototype
helpCommand_
args
length
print
'warning: arguments to \'help\' are ignored'
'Note: <> denotes symbollic values to be replaced with real values.'
'Note: [] denotes optional parts of commands, or optional options / arguments.'
'      e.g. d[elete] - you get the same command if you type d or delete.'
''
'[break] - break as soon as possible'
'b[reak] location [condition]'
'        - break on named function: location is a function name'
'        - break on function: location is #<id>#'
'        - break on script position: location is name:line[:column]'
'clear <breakpoint #>       - deletes the specified user defined breakpoint'
'd[elete]  <breakpoint #>   - deletes the specified user defined breakpoint'
'dis[able] <breakpoint #>   - disables the specified user defined breakpoint'
'dis[able] exc[eptions] [[all] | unc[aught]]'
'                           - disables breaking on exceptions'
'en[able]  <breakpoint #>   - enables the specified user defined breakpoint'
'en[able]  exc[eptions] [[all] | unc[aught]]'
'                           - enables breaking on exceptions'
'b[ack]t[race] [n] | [-n] | [from to]'
'                           - prints the stack back trace'
'f[rame]                    - prints info about the current frame context'
'f[rame] <frame #>          - set context to specified frame #'
'scopes'
'scope <scope #>'
'up                         - set context to caller of current frame'
'do[wn]                     - set context to callee of current frame'
'inf[o] br[eak]             - prints info about breakpoints in use'
'inf[o] ar[gs]              - prints info about arguments of the current function'
'inf[o] lo[cals]            - prints info about locals in the current function'
'inf[o] liveobjectlist|lol  - same as \'lol info\''
'step [in | next | out| min [step count]]'
'c[ontinue]                 - continue executing after a breakpoint'
's[tep]   [<N>]             - step into the next N callees (default N is 1)'
's[tep]i  [<N>]             - step into the next N callees (default N is 1)'
'n[ext]   [<N>]             - step over the next N callees (default N is 1)'
'fin[ish] [<N>]             - step out of N frames (default N is 1)'
'p[rint] <expression>       - prints the result of the specified expression'
'dir <expression>           - prints the object structure of the result'
'set <var> = <expression>   - executes the specified statement'
'l[ist]                     - list the source code around for the current pc'
'l[ist] [- | <start>,<end>] - list the specified range of source code'
'source [from line [num lines]]'
'scr[ipts] [native|extensions|all]'
'scr[ipts] [<filter text>]  - list scripts with the specified text in its description'
'gc                         - runs the garbage collector'
lol_is_enabled
'liveobjectlist|lol <command> - live object list tracking.'
'  where <command> can be:'
'  c[apture]               - captures a LOL list.'
'  clear|del[ete] <id>|all - clears LOL of id <id>.'
'                            If \'all\' is unspecified instead, will clear all.'
'  diff <id1> <id2> [<dump options>]'
'                          - prints the diff between LOLs id1 and id2.'
'                          - also see <dump options> below.'
'  getid <address>         - gets the obj id for the specified address if available.'
'                            The address must be in hex form prefixed with 0x.'
'  inf[o] [<N>]            - lists summary info of all LOL lists.'
'                            If N is specified, will print N items at a time.'
'  [l[ist]] <id> [<dump options>]'
'                          - prints the listing of objects in LOL id.'
'  reset                   - clears all LOL lists.'
'  ret[ainers] <id> [<dump options>]'
'                          - prints the list of retainers of obj id.'
'  path <id1> <id2>        - prints the retaining path from obj id1 to id2.'
'                            If only one id is specified, will print the path from'
'                            roots to the specified object if available.'
'  print <id>              - prints the obj for the specified obj id if available.'
''
'  <dump options> includes:'
'     [v[erbose]]            - do verbose dump.'
'     [<N>]                  - dump N items at a time.  Implies verbose dump.'
'                             If unspecified, N will default to '
kDefaultLolLinesToPrintAtATime
'.  Max N is '
kMaxLolLinesToPrintAtATime
'.'
'     [i[ndex] <i>]          - start dump from index i.  Implies verbose dump.'
'     [t[ype] <type>]        - filter by type.'
'     [sp[ace] <space name>] - filter by heap space where <space name> is one of'
cell
code

'     If the verbose option, or an option that implies a verbose dump'
'     is specified, then a verbose dump will requested.  Else, a summary dump'
